If your problem is
maximize profit = gains − costs,
rewrite it as
TOTAL − penalties,
then minimize penalties with min cut.

-------------------------------------
Standard modeling patterns

   - Choose / Not Choose (Project Selection)
       - Choosing item i gives profit +p_i
       - Skipping it loses that profit
       - S → item_i (capacity = p_i)
       - Cut edge → item NOT chosen → pay p_i
       - Don’t cut → item chosen

   - Cost for choosing something
       - Choosing object j costs c_j
       - object_j → T (capacity = c_j)
       - Cut edge → object chosen → pay c_j
       - Don’t cut → not chosen

   - Dependency (must choose B if choose A)
       - If A is chosen, B must also be chosen
       - A → B (capacity = ∞)
       - Prevents cut where A is chosen but B is not



   Only capacities	-> Max Flow
   Gains & costs	-> Min Cut
   Assignment with profits ->Min-Cost Max-Flow
   Bipartite matching -> Max Flow
   Dependencies + profits -> 	Min Cut